{
  "texts": [
    "Qwen-32B refers to Qwen/Qwen3-32B [27], Coder-32B refers to Qwen/Qwen2.5-Coder-32B-Instruct [24], Math-7B refers to https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen2.5-Math-7B-Instruct [25], Math-72B refers Qwen/Qwen2.5-Math-72B-Instruct [25], and Llama-70B refers to meta-llama/Llama-3.3-70B-Instruct [26].",
    "Compared to other strong foundation models, Orchestrator-8B achieves better results (Table 1) while making few calls to GPT-5..8 1.2 1.6 Nemontron-49B 5.1 1.6 0.5 0.8 0.1 0.1 0.3 0.7 0.9 1.4 Llama-3.3-70B 1.8 0.0 0.1 0.0 1.4 0.3 4.8 0.6 1.4 1.3 Qwen3-235B-A22B 6.2 0.3 0.6 1.2 0.6 0.1 1.1 1.4 1.0 2.2 Claude Opus 4.1 6.2 0.2 0.3 0.3 0.1 0.0 0.1 1.0 1.3 1.4 GPT-5 2.7 5.6 0.0 0.2 0.0 0.0 0.0 0.5 0.7 1.0 Orchestrator-8B 1.6 1.7 1.3 0.2 0.0 0.1 0.0 1.8 0.7 0.8 Calculation of rewards for preference-aware benchmark During training, we directly follow the Equation 2 to calculate rewards.",
    "In the evaluation, we use the following procedure.",
    "Following the definition in §3.2, we have a tool set {𝑡 1, 𝑡 2,..., 𝑡 𝑛 } and a rollout trajectory 𝜏, we consider the vector 𝑀 𝜏 = [𝑚 𝜏 𝑡1, 𝑚 𝜏 𝑡2,..., 𝑚 𝜏 𝑡𝑛, 𝑟 𝜏 outcome, 𝑟 𝜏 compute, 𝑟 𝜏 latency], where 𝑚 𝜏 𝑡• is the number of times tool 𝑡 • is invoked in 𝜏.",
    "In the evaluation, we obtain the baseline vector 𝑀 0 by running the starting checkpoint, e.g., Qwen3-8B."
